Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Spread the @McCain Home Chips{400%grams} on a #baking tray{} in a single layer.
Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

When the oven is hot, bake the chips on the top shelf, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn
halfway through.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, add the @mayonnaise{32%grams}, @chipotle paste{20%grams}
(add less if you'd prefer things milder) and @honey{1/2%tbsp}. Mix well and set
aside.

In a #large bowl{}, combine the @red wine vinegar{12%milliliter(s)}, @sugar{1/2%tsp}
and @olive oil{1%tbsp}(for the dressing). Season with @salt{1/4%tsp} and @pepper{}.
Add the @coleslaw mix{120%grams} and toss to coat in the dressing, then set aside.

Drain the @fish pie mix{1%pack} and pat dry with #kitchen paper{}.

When the chips have about 10 mins remaining, add the fish mix to a #medium bowl{}.
Add the @Mexican style spice mix{1%sachet}, @salt{} and @plain flour{1%tbsp} and
toss to coat the pieces.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish.

Heat a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat with a generous drizzle of @oil{}.

Once hot, add the fish to the pan and fry, turning the pieces regularly, until
golden and crispy, ~{6-8%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when opaque in the middle. Remove from the heat.

Meanwhile, pop the @plain taco tortillas{4} into the oven to warm through,
~{1-2%minutes}.

When everything's ready, share the tortillas between your plates (2 per person).
Spread over the chipotle mayo, then top with the coleslaw and Mexican spiced fish.
Serve the chips alongside.

Enjoy!